BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
19
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
20
This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Abolition of
21
Abortion Act".
22
SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
23
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 16414 Page 1

1 Acknowledging the sanctity of innocent human life, created in
2 the image of God, the purpose of this act is to:
3 1. Follow the United States Constitution, which requires that
4 "no state...shall deny to any person within its jurisdiction the
5 equal protection of the laws";
6 2. Fulfill such constitutional requirement by protecting the
7 lives of preborn persons with the same criminal and civil laws
8 protecting the lives of born persons by repealing provisions that
9 permit willful prenatal homicide or assault;
10 3. Protect pregnant mothers from being pressured to abort by
11 repealing provisions that may otherwise allow a person to direct,
12 advise, encourage, or solicit a mother to abort her child; and
13 4. Ensure that all persons potentially subject to such laws are
14 entitled to due process protections.
15 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 696 of Title 21, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. This section applies even where the victim is an unborn
19 child.
20 B. Enforcement of sections 642 through 650.11 and sections 691
21 through 695 of this title of the Oklahoma Statutes where the victim
22 is an unborn child is subject to the same presumptions, defenses,
23 justifications, laws of parties, immunities, and clemencies as would
24 apply when the victim is a person who had been born alive.
Req. No. 16414 Page 2

1 C. This section shall not apply to:
2 1. The undertaking of life-saving procedures to save the life
3 of the mother when accompanied by reasonable steps to save the life
4 of the unborn child; or
5 2. A spontaneous miscarriage.
6 D. This section prevails over other law to the extent of any
7 conflict.
8 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 12 O.S. 2021, Section 1053, is
9 amended to read as follows:
10 Section 1053. A. When the death of one is caused by the
11 wrongful act or omission of another, the personal representative of
12 the former may maintain an action therefor against the latter, or
13 his or her personal representative if he or she is also deceased, if
14 the former might have maintained an action, had he or she lived,
15 against the latter, or his or her representative, for an injury for
16 the same act or omission. The action must be commenced within two
17 (2) years.
18 B. The damages recoverable in actions for wrongful death as
19 provided in this section shall include the following:
20 1. Medical and burial expenses, which shall be distributed to
21 the person or governmental agency as defined in Section 5051.1 of
22 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes who paid these expenses, or to the
23 decedent's estate if paid by the estate. The provisions of this
24
Req. No. 16414 Page 3

1 para graph shall not apply to the cost of an abortion in actions
2 maintained pursuant to subsection F of this section;
3 2. The loss of consortium and the grief of the surviving
4 spouse, which shall be distributed to the surviving spouse;
5 3. The mental pain and anguish suffered by the decedent, which
6 shall be distributed to the surviving spouse and children, if any,
7 or next of kin in the same proportion as personal property of the
8 decedent. For the purposes of actions maintained pursuant to
9 subsection F of this section, "next of kin" next of kin as used in
10 this paragraph shall mean the parent or grandparent who maintained
11 the action as provided for in paragraph 3 of subsection F of this
12 section;
13 4. The pecuniary loss to the survivors based upon properly
14 admissible evidence with regard thereto including, but not limited
15 to, the age, occupation, earning capacity, health habits, and
16 probable duration of the decedent's life, which must inure to the
17 exclusive benefit of the surviving spouse and children, if any, or
18 next of kin, and shall be distributed to them according to their
19 pecuniary loss. For the purposes of actions maintained pursuant to
20 subsection F of this section, "next of kin" next of kin as used in
21 this paragraph shall mean the parent or grandparent who maintained
22 the action as provided for in paragraph 3 of subsection F of this
23 section; and
24
Req. No. 16414 Page 4

1 5. The grief and loss of companionship of the children and
2 parents of the decedent, which shall be distributed to them
3 according to their grief and loss of companionship.
4 C. In proper cases, as provided by Section 9.1 of Title 23 of
5 the Oklahoma Statutes, punitive or exemplary damages may also be
6 recovered against the person proximately causing the wrongful death
7 or the person's representative if such person is deceased. Such
8 damages, if recovered, shall be distributed to the surviving spouse
9 and children, if any, or next of kin in the same proportion as
10 personal property of the decedent. For the purposes of actions
11 maintained pursuant to subsection F of this section, "next of kin"
12 next of kin as used in this paragraph shall mean the parent or
13 grandparent who maintained the action as provided for in paragraph 3
14 of subsection F of this section.
15 D. Where the recovery is to be distributed according to a
16 person's pecuniary loss or loss of companionship, the judge shall
17 determine the proper division.
18 E. The above-mentioned distributions shall be made after the
19 payment of legal expenses and costs of the action.
20 F. 1. The provisions of this section shall also be available
21 for the death of an unborn person as defined in Section 1-730 of
22 Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
23 2. The provisions of this subsection shall apply to acts which
24 cause the death of an unborn person in utero if:
Req. No. 16414 Page 5

1 a. the physician who performed the abortion or the
2 referring physician fails to obtain and document the
3 voluntary and informed consent of the pregnant woman
4 pursuant to Section 1-738.2 of Title 63 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes,
6 b. the pregnant woman withdraws her consent to the
7 abortion prior to performance of the abortion,
8 c. the pregnant woman undergoes the abortion due to
9 coercion from a third party,
10 d. the physician fails to obtain and document proof of
11 age demonstrating that the pregnant woman is not a
12 minor, or, in the case of a minor, fails to obtain:
13 (1) parental consent to the abortion pursuant to
14 Section 1-740.2 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma
15 Statutes,
16 (2) proof that the pregnant woman, although a minor,
17 is emancipated, or
18 (3) judicial authorization of the abortion without
19 parental notification pursuant to Section 1-740.3
20 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
21 e. the physician who performed the abortion causes the
22 woman physical or psychological harm, the possibility
23 of which she did not foresee or was not informed of at
24 the time of her consent,
Req. No. 16414 Page 6

1 f. the physician who performed the abortion fails to
2 screen the pregnant woman and document such screening
3 for risk factors associated with a heightened risk of
4 adverse consequences from abortion which a reasonably
5 prudent physician would screen for,
6 g. the physician fails to screen the pregnant woman and
7 document such screening for physical or psychological
8 impairment of judgment due to factors including, but
9 not limited to, drugs, alcohol, illness or fatigue,
10 h. the physician fraudulently induces the pregnant woman
11 to obtain the abortion or gives misleading or false
12 information in response to a pregnant woman's inquiry,
13 or
14 i. there exist any other circumstances which violate
15 state law.
16 The provisions of this paragraph shall not be construed to apply
17 to cases in which a physician licensed to practice medicine in this
18 state attempts, in a reasonably prudent manner, to prevent the death
19 of an unborn person or a pregnant woman.
20 3. A parent or grandparent of the deceased unborn person is
21 entitled to maintain an action against the physician person who
22 caused the death of an unborn person under the conditions provided
23 by subparagraphs a through i of paragraph 2 of this subsection;
24 provided, however, the parent or grandparent may not maintain such
Req. No. 16414 Page 7

1 acti on if the parent or grandparent coerced the mother of the unborn
2 person to abort the unborn person.
3 4. Liability for wrongful death by the physician under this
4 section shall not be waived by the pregnant woman prior to
5 performance of the abortion. A physician shall not request, orally,
6 on a written form or in any other manner, that the pregnant woman
7 waive the liability of the physician for wrongful death related to
8 the abortion as a condition of performing an abortion.
9 5. Under no circumstances shall the mother of the unborn person
10 be found liable for causing the death of the unborn person unless
11 the mother has committed a crime that caused the death of the unborn
12 person.
13 SECTION 5. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 691, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 691. A. Homicide is the killing of one human being by
16 another.
17 B. As used in this section, "human being" includes an unborn
18 child, as defined in Section 1-730 of Title 63 of the Oklahoma
19 Statutes.
20 C. Homicide shall not include:
21 1. Acts which cause the death of an unborn child if those acts
22 were committed during a legal abortion to which the pregnant woman
23 consented; or
24
Req. No. 16414 Page 8

1 2. Acts acts which are committed pursuant to the usual and
2 customary standards of medical practice during diagnostic testing or
3 therapeutic treatment.
4 D. Under no circumstances shall the mother of the unborn child
5 be prosecuted for causing the death of the unborn child unless the
6 mother has committed a crime that caused the death of the unborn
7 child.
8 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
9 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
10 The provisions of this act shall not be retroactive.
11 SECTION 7. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
